# DEBUG_LOG discipline (v2.0)

This project follows the [debug-log-skill](https://github.com/<you>/debug-log-skill) protocol v2.0. Before writing any non-trivial code, and after fixing any bug, obey the rules below.

## Before coding — active pre-flight

**Do not read `DEBUG_LOG.md` end-to-end.** Grep it for what matches the task:

```bash
# By file path (strongest signal)
grep -niE "path/to/File\.ext" DEBUG_LOG.md

# By tag (see references/tag-taxonomy.md in the skill folder)
grep -niE "#Compose|#StateFlow" DEBUG_LOG.md

# By Root Cause Category (the 14 canonical categories)
grep -niE "Race Condition|Scope Leak|LLM Hallucination" DEBUG_LOG.md
```

Read only the entries grep surfaces plus those they cross-reference.

Then:

1. Read `references/<track>.md` for each track the project uses, plus `references/cross-cutting.md` and `references/tag-taxonomy.md`.
2. For new features, also work through `references/preempt-checklist.md` and `references/pre-mortem-workflow.md`.
3. State a plan: goal, files touched, interfaces preserved, DL numbers with applicable prevention rules, verification approach.

